Introduction

Elkie is a Hong Kong singer-songwriter and actress under her own company KEYMAXii, formed in 2021.

On February 23, 2016, Elkie was announced as one of the two new members of the South Korean girl group CLC under Cube Entertainment. After promoting for almost 5 years with the group, it was announced on December 25, 2020, that Elkie had submitted a request to terminate her contract with Cube Entertainment, citing lack of payment and support for the group's development, implying the company has no plans for Elkie's future.

On February 3, 2021, it was announced that she had officially left the group and Cube Entertainment as her contract with the agency was terminated in a mutual agreement. After the group's state was unknown for a while, Seungyeon said In June of 2022 that CLC didn't disband, it was unknown if that statement also included Elkie as she had originally left the group. However, Sorn confirmed in an interview that CLC was still a 7-member group, confirming that Elkie was still a part of the lineup.

Elkie made her solo debut on November 23, 2018, with the digital single "I Dream".

In October 2023, she participated in the Taiwanese reality survival show Show Up Girls where she ended up ranking 1st place.
